    LeoManager¶狮子座经理¶

    1. LeoManager's Master / Slave managementLeoManager的Master/Slave管理

    2. There is no clear definition on how the system works if slave node is not present. Since you can't see slave node in "leofs-adm status" command, it's pretty unobvious what actually changes when you launch it. Nothing appears in status commands, nothing appears in log files on management node.如果从节点不存在，系统如何工作没有明确的定义。由于您在“leofs-adm status”命令中看不到从属节点，因此启动它时实际发生的变化并不明显。状态命令中没有任何内容，管理节点上的日志文件中也没有任何内容。

      • Will document how it works while slave node is not present.将记录在从节点不存在时它是如何工作的。
      • Will provide information on how to check on health of slave node except SNMP (more simpler way)将提供有关如何检查除 SNMP 之外的从属节点健康状况的信息（更简单的方法）

    3. by default, leofs-adm isn't working on slave node! It took me quite a time to realize (by looking at leo-center) that you actually can connect to slave node with leofs-adm, only with default config you have to specify different port.默认情况下，leofs-adm 不在从属节点上工作！我花了很长时间才意识到（通过查看 leo-center）您实际上可以使用 leofs-adm 连接到从节点，只有在默认配置下您必须指定不同的端口。

      • Will document and preferably generate a leofs-adm for slave when do make release将记录并最好在 make release 时为 slave 生成​​ leofs-adm

    4. However, when you specify port, leofs-adm output changes to JSON style and there is no obvious way to get same output as you get from the master node.. confusing. This should be mentioned in documentation, that leofs-adm works with slave node (at first I thought it just won't work at all), but default configuration sets different management port for slave.但是，当您指定端口时，leofs-adm 输出会更改为 JSON 样式，并且没有明显的方法来获得与您从主节点获得的相同输出……令人困惑。这应该在文档中提到，leofs-adm 与从节点一起工作（起初我认为它根本不起作用），但默认配置为从节点设置了不同的管理端口。

      • Will document that there are two ports in each manager, the one is formatted in text for console, the another one is formatted in json for api (machine readalbe one)将记录每个管理器中有两个端口，一个用于控制台的文本格式，另一个用于 api 的 json 格式（机器读取一个）

    5. Configuration guide - fundamentals配置指南 - 基础

    6. The consistency level is configured in this file. It should not be modified while the system is running." I believe this should be rephrased somewhat.一致性级别在此文件中配置。它不应该在系统运行时被修改。”我认为这应该稍微改写一下。
      • Yes. should be rephrased by "consistency.num_of_replicas should not be modified while the system is running.""是的。应该改写为“consistency.num_of_replicas should not be modified while the system is running.”
    7. What would happen if I'm to actually modify it while system is running? and Which parts of system I'm supposed to restart if I'm to change it in this file? Also it kind of gives impression that it's not possible to modify consistency level on running system, but there is "leofs-adm update-consistency-level" command for that!如果我在系统运行时实际修改它会发生什么？以及如果我要在此文件中更改它，我应该重新启动系统的哪些部分？此外，它给人的印象是无法在正在运行的系统上修改一致性级别，但是有“leofs-adm update-consistency-level”命令可以做到这一点！
      • Will document that what would happen when modifying consistency.num_of_replicas while system is running and which parts of system should be restarted to reflect changes将记录在系统运行时修改 consistency.num_of_replicas 时会发生什么，以及应该重新启动系统的哪些部分以反映更改
      • Will document that if you want changes to be temporal, just do update-consistency-level将记录如果您希望更改是暂时的，只需执行 update-consistency-level
      • Will document that if you want changes to be parmanent, edit the section of consistency.* in leo_manager.conf and also do update-consistency-level that distributes the change to all of the members without forcing them to restart.将记录如果您希望更改是永久的，请编辑 leo_manager.conf 中的 consistency.* 部分，并执行 update-consistency-level 将更改分发给所有成员而不强制他们重新启动。
    8. "consistency.rack_aware_replicas # of rack-aware replicas" - there is no information about what it does“consistency.rack_aware_replicas # of rack-aware replicas”——没有关于它做什么的信息
      • Will document the details将记录细节

    LeoStorage¶Leo存储¶

    1. Configuration guide - LeoStorage配置指南-LeoStorage

    2. "You cannot modify the following LeoStorage configurations after launched a system(LeoFS) because the algorithm of retrieving object depends on their configurations, that means Leo Storage cannot handle objects." but what if I do want to modify these parameters? This is rather practical problem, say, I need to add few new paths to obj_containers.path. Right now there is no explanation how to accomplish it correctly, only this warning which tells you not to do this.“您不能在启动系统（LeoFS）后修改以下 LeoStorage 配置，因为检索对象的算法取决于它们的配置，这意味着 Leo Storage 无法处理对象。”但是如果我确实想修改这些参数怎么办？这是一个相当实际的问题，比如说，我需要向 obj_containers.path 添加一些新路径。现在没有解释如何正确完成它，只有这个警告告诉你不要这样做。

      • Short version: as described at the current docs, there is no easy way to accomplish modifying what you want简短版本：如当前文档所述，没有简单的方法来完成您想要的修改
      • Long version a specific answer to adding new paths to obj_containers.path: unfortunately just adding new paths don't work instead you have to do the following. (you have to do the same procedure if you want to modify obj_containers.num_of_containers长版本是将新路径添加到 obj_containers.path 的特定答案：不幸的是，仅添加新路径是行不通的，您必须执行以下操作。 （如果你想修改 obj_containers.num_of_containers，你必须做同样的程序
        1. Suspend and stop the target server and backup -r under avs dir挂起和停止目标服务器，并在avs目录下备份-r
        2. Edit the obj_containers.path in leo_storage.conf编辑 leo_storage.conf 中的 obj_containers.path
        3. Remove -rf under avs dir删除 avs 目录下的 -rf
        4. Restart and resume the server重新启动并恢复服务器
        5. Do leofs-adm recover-node执行 leofs-adm 恢复节点

    3. Architecture - LeoStorage架构-LeoStorage

    4. Lots of topics where extra documentation would help are already listed in LeoFS Issue#532LeoFS Issue#532 中已经列出了很多需要额外文档帮助的主题
      • Will do #532 ASAP会尽快做#532

    5. I'd like to add that information about how and when storage nodes do fsync() for data files is missing. Is it done after writing every object? Or on timer? Is it configurable?我想添加有关存储节点如何以及何时为数据文件执行 fsync() 的信息丢失。是不是每个对象都写完了？还是定时器？它是可配置的吗？

      • Now no explicit call file:fsync because even if we call fsync some blocks can be still on the volatile place (the disk controller can choose not to obey that which unfortunately many disks choose to) but we will consider to take it another look as at least it increase a possibility to be placed at a real permanent one现在没有显式调用 file:fsync 因为即使我们调用 fsync 一些块仍然可以在易失性地方（磁盘控制器可以选择不服从不幸的是许多磁盘选择的）但我们会考虑再看看它至少它增加了被安置在一个真正永久的可能性

    6. Best Practices最佳实践

    7. how vital is queue in work/queue directory? I mean, obviously data on storage node itself won't be lost if this queue is lost or damaged; but under load, there is information related to replication and such in these messages, right?工作/队列目录中的队列有多重要？我的意思是，显然如果这个队列丢失或损坏，存储节点本身的数据不会丢失；但是在负载下，这些消息中有与复制等相关的信息，对吗？
      • Yes a message in queue may have information related to replication是的，队列中的消息可能包含与复制相关的信息

    8. If they are suddenly lost on some node, are any extra steps needed to recover anything that might've been lost?如果它们在某个节点上突然丢失，是否需要任何额外的步骤来恢复可能丢失的任何东西？

      • Yes. you need some extra steps to recover any files that don't satisfy the redundancy requirement specified at consistency.num_of_replicas in leo_manager.conf. we'd like to answer what the extra step actually is at your another question "scrub of data"是的。您需要一些额外的步骤来恢复任何不满足 leo_manager.conf 中 consistency.num_of_replicas 指定的冗余要求的文件。我们想回答您的另一个问题“数据清理”中的额外步骤实际上是什么

    9. Regarding all kinds of metadata (mnesia on management nodes, leveldb queues on all nodes, leveldb metadata on storage nodes) it would be nice to have some information about their possible size and I/O required for that. I mean, it might be obvious how to estimate size of main storage and possible to make guesses about I/O load on AVS files, but exactly how much space various kinds of metadata can consume on loaded production systems? And whether it might require lots of extra I/O, e.g. HDD for main storage + SSD for metadata or something. If most users shouldn't worry about this - it's fine too, but a brief note like "metadata does not require lots of I/O and queues shouldn't consume more than 100 MB, metadata for AVS files - estimate is bytes per stored record" would be great to have.关于所有类型的元数据（管理节点上的 mnesia、所有节点上的 leveldb 队列、存储节点上的 leveldb 元数据），最好能获得一些关于它们可能的大小和为此所需的 I/O 的信息。我的意思是，如何估计主存储的大小并可能猜测 AVS 文件上的 I/O 负载可能是显而易见的，但是各种元数据在加载的生产系统上究竟可以占用多少空间？以及它是否可能需要大量额外的 I/O，例如用于主存储的 HDD + 用于元数据或其他东西的 SSD。如果大多数用户不应该担心这个 - 这也很好，但是像“元数据不需要大量 I/O 和队列不应该消耗超过 100 MB，AVS 文件的元数据 - 估计是每个存储的字节数记录”会很棒。

      • Great point especially for loaded production sysmtes. we can't provide actual numbers right now but can say that metadata using leveldb can consume your I/O load more than expected due to its compaction activity. part of problems we encountered has been fixed at LeoFS Issue#555 and also we are now tackling at LeoFS Issue#503. We will publish the actual number (extra space, # of size, I/O load etc) ASAP特别是对于加载的生产系统来说很重要。我们现在无法提供实际数字，但可以说使用 leveldb 的元数据由于其压缩活动会比预期消耗更多的 I/O 负载。我们遇到的部分问题已在 LeoFS Issue#555 中修复，我们现在也在 LeoFS Issue#503 中解决。我们将尽快公布实际数量（额外空间、大小、I/O 负载等）

    10. Of course, whether I/O on metadata and queues size might become an issue during rebalance and recover-node operations should be mentioned as well.当然，在重新平衡和恢复节点操作期间，元数据和队列大小的 I/O 是否可能成为一个问题也应该被提及。

      • Will provide the some reference number to estimate the approximate load将提供一些参考数字来估计大概的负载

    11. If there is single obj_containers.path per huge drive (e.g. 8 TB), then with default setting of 8 containers it will create up to 1 TB AVS files (well, not really but..). Since file has to be rewritten during compaction, it would really suck. I think some recommendations about single file size / number of containers should be provided, because it's really hard to guess which size to prefer here and if there are downsides of having lots of containers and smaller files. Even something vague like "we recommend to pick number of containers so that single file size will be in 20-200 GB range" would help - thus users would know that they should pick the number of containers in 40-400 range for said 8 TB drives. There is no need to guide the users by hand, just brief information of advantages and disadvantages of having huge files and few containers vs. smaller files and lots of containers. Like, maybe having lots of containers would require extra memory and resources, and having each container too huge would cause problems with leveldb metadata storage.如果每个巨大的驱动器（例如 8 TB）只有一个 obj_containers.path，那么在默认设置为 8 个容器的情况下，它将创建多达 1 TB 的 AVS 文件（好吧，不是真的但是......）。由于在压缩过程中必须重写文件，这真的很糟糕。我认为应该提供一些关于单个文件大小/容器数量的建议，因为真的很难猜测这里更喜欢哪种大小，以及是否有很多容器和较小文件的缺点。即使像“我们建议选择容器数量，以便单个文件大小在 20-200 GB 范围内”这样模糊的内容也会有所帮助——因此用户会知道他们应该为所述 8 TB 选择 40-400 范围内的容器数量驱动器。无需手动指导用户，只需简要介绍大文件和少量容器与小文件和大量容器的优缺点。比如，可能有很多容器需要额外的内存和资源，而每个容器太大会导致 leveldb 元数据存储出现问题。

      • There is a FAQ but have not covered all topics you want to know so we will update this FAQ有一个常见问题解答，但没有涵盖您想要了解的所有主题，因此我们将更新此常见问题解答

    12. num_of_vnodes - should this parameter ever be changed? (e.g. when having lots of storage nodes or lots of containers per node).num_of_vnodes - 这个参数应该改变吗？ （例如，当每个节点有很多存储节点或很多容器时）。

      • There is a logic that calculate an appropriate num_of_vnodes based on some facts like # of maximum storage nodes, # of maximum objects and so on. @yosukehara will answer later.有一种逻辑可以根据一些事实（例如最大存储节点数、最大对象数等）计算适当的 num_of_vnodes。 @yosukehara 稍后会回答。

    13. How data is distributed between AVS files - equal amount per file? In other words, if, say, I have nodes - 8 drives, 1 TB each but at some point started to add nodes - 8 drivers, 2 TB each, am I supposed to double amount of containers on these new nodes in order to utilize these 2 TB of data (I understand it would be bad from I/O point of view, of course)? Or it's more complicated than that?数据如何在 AVS 文件之间分配 - 每个文件的数量相等？换句话说，如果我有节点——8 个驱动器，每个 1 TB，但在某个时候开始添加节点——8 个驱动器，每个 2 TB，我是否应该将这些新节点上的容器数量加倍以便利用这些 2 TB 的数据（当然，我知道从 I/O 的角度来看这会很糟糕）？或者比这更复杂？

      • Equal amount per file. Setting the appropriate value to num_of_vnodes on the corresponding node should solve the problem - deviation of disk space by node每个文件的数量相等。在相应节点上为 num_of_vnodes 设置适当的值应该可以解决问题 - 节点磁盘空间偏差

    LeoGateway¶Leo网关¶

    1. Configuration guide - LeoGateway配置指南-LeoGateway
    2. there is a problem which made me stumble for quite some time. I created a copy of leo_gateway directory for testing NFS and S3 gateways along with REST. I configured them to different ports, including SNMP ports and such but for some reason I just couldn't launch REST and S3 gateways together. NFS + REST - fine, NFS + S3 - fine, but REST + S3 - didn't work. They both launched fine, but the one launched later simply refused to work (also, it had status of "stopped" in leofs-adm). Turned out, I have copied leo_gateway directory to leo_s3_gateway after launching it once.. and there was something in work/queue/membership that made these two gateways "the same" - despite having different node names. After removing that directory from one of the nodes and re-launching it it worked fine.有一个问题让我绊倒了很长一段时间。我创建了一个 leo_gateway 目录的副本，用于测试 NFS 和 S3 网关以及 REST。我将它们配置到不同的端口，包括 SNMP 端口等，但出于某种原因，我无法同时启动 REST 和 S3 网关。 NFS + REST - 很好，NFS + S3 - 很好，但 REST + S3 - 没用。它们都启动良好，但后来启动的那个根本无法工作（而且，它在 leofs-adm 中的状态为“已停止”）。事实证明，我在启动一次后将 leo_gateway 目录复制到 leo_s3_gateway .. 工作/队列/成员资格中有一些东西使这两个网关“相同” - 尽管具有不同的节点名称。从其中一个节点中删除该目录并重新启动它后，它工作正常。
      • Will consider to add this knowledge to the FAQ section.将考虑将此知识添加到常见问题解答部分。
